        new TestedOpcode(0x0017, "REQUEST_TARGET",
            "Opcodes/SectorRequestTargetTests.cs RequestTarget_OnNullTarget_ReceivesSetTargetWithSentinelTargetIdMinusOne — client sends a canonical 8-byte RequestTarget payload {int32 GameID=0; int32 TargetID=0} on the sector connection after STAGE handshake completes. Server Player::HandleRequestTarget (server/src/PlayerConnection.cpp:3390) unconditionally calls SendSetTarget(request->TargetID, -1) regardless of whether the target exists — for TargetID=0 the GetObjectFromID(0) lookups return null for both newtarget and oldtarget, m_ProspectWindow is false on a fresh starbase character so OpenInterface is skipped, BlankVerbs is a safe memset, and the threat-rank logic is gated on newtarget != null so it's also skipped. The mandatory SetTarget reply makes this a direct positive-correlation test instead of a survival probe — we assert the 0x0019 SET_TARGET payload is exactly 8B, that the reply GameID equals our request TargetID (0), and that the reply TargetID equals the hard-coded -1 sentinel that SendSetTarget emits. Catches: (a) PacketStructures.h RequestTarget long-revert regression (currently 2× int32_t = 8B canonical; if widened to long the struct grows to 12B and TargetID reads from past end of 8B wire payload into garbage); (b) PacketStructures.h SetTarget reply long-revert (caught by payload-length-8 assert); (c) reply field-order swap (caught by TargetID==-1 assert — the literal would appear in GameID slot instead); (d) proxy default-case ForwardClientOpcode dropping the opcode (0x0017 is not explicitly listed in proxy/ClientToServer_linux_stubs.cpp); (e) server→client UDP fan-out regression in the SendOpcode→SendPacketCache→0x2016 PACKET_SEQUENCE→proxy SendClientPacketSequence→TCP path; (f) dispatcher mis-route at server/src/PlayerConnection.cpp:443. Per CLAUDE.md server-integrity: the wire shape and the -1 sentinel reply are exactly what retail emits when the user clicks empty space to clear the active target."),
