t broke the SendOpcode header width (already fixed Phase K) would re-emerge here. Per CLAUDE.md server-integrity: the wire shape is exactly what retail Win32 client emits when the user toggles a ship-equipment ItemState; the UNRECOGNISED-error path is exactly retail's response to an out-of-spec Inventory byte (the LogMessage + \"Please submit a bug report\" string is the verbatim retail error message). We are not making the server accept any new input shape and not fabricating any reply."),
